Table 2

The suture line of specimen MB.C.29674 has a short external lobe with concave flanks and bifid prongs (
Fig. 17D
). The ventrolateral saddle is asymmetric and appears dorsally inclined. The adventive lobe is semicircular in shape with twelve small notches of equal size. In contrast to this is the lateral lobe almost flat at its base; it is also serrated by numerous small notches.

Upper part of the Hambast Formation; 5.20 to 4.70 m below the extinction horizon (
Shevyrevites shevyrevi Zone
).

